CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 4, 1960, pg.23 reads: "Top Life Underwriters - Four of Pittsburgh's top insurance life underwriters received trophies at the Loendi Club for having the highest sales records of the four companies celebrating National Insurance Week in Pittsburgh. Left to right: Richard Robinson, North Carolina Mutual; Edward A. Palm, manager and chairman of the awards committee, presenting the trophies; Lottie Y. Luby, American Woodmen; James E. Jones, Supreme Liberty Life, and David Lester, Provident Home Industrial Mutual. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of men and women seated in chairs, including, from left: Edward A. Palm, Offerell Johnson, and U.E. Finley, seated in front row, gathered in Loendi Club for National Insurance Week celebration
